tafsir[17]{c,v,t}:
  91,1,"By the sun and his morning brightness"
  91,3,"and by the day when it displays him"
  91,4,"and by the night when it enshrouds him!"
  91,5,"By the heaven and That which built it"
  91,6,"and by the earth and That which extended it!"
  91,8,"and inspired it to lewdness and godfearing!"
  91,10,"and failed has he who seduces it."
  91,11,"Thamood cried lies in their insolence"
  91,15,"and He fears not the issue thereof."
  92,1,"By the night enshrouding"
  92,2,"and the day in splendour"
  92,4,"surely your striving is to diverse ends."
  92,5,"As for him who gives and is godfearing"
  92,7,"We shall surely ease him to the Easing."
  92,10,"We shall surely ease him to the Hardship;"
  92,11,"his wealth shall not avail him when he perishes."
  92,13,"and to Us belong the Last and the First."